Requirements:

- C compiler
- Gtk+ version 2.0 or higher [http://www.gtk.org]
- GD verison 2.0 (optional, for PNG output) [http://www.boutell.com/gd]


Installation:

1. tar xzvf microdef-xyz.tar.gz
2. cd microdef
3. make
4. cp microdef /any/place/you/want


Installation using configure script:

1. tar xzvf microdef-xyz.tar.gz
2. cd microdef
3. autoreconf --install
4. ./configure --prefix=/any/place/you/want
5. make && sudo make install


Problems:

If you don't have the GD library, please remove the "-DGDGUI" and "-lgd"
statements in the file called Makefile. 

Note: There is no possibility to use GD with "configure".
